<div class="flex flex-col gap-5">
	<p>
		Blurring the lines between fashion media and digital art, Costas Kazantzis creates immersive virtual environments that reimagine how garments, bodies, and identity exist in digital space. With a background in fashion media and computer engineering, their work transforms clothing into atmosphere, gesture, and storytelling—designing worlds where garments don't follow gravity or logic but can glitch, dissolve, or behave like weather.
	</p>
	<p>
		Their approach to fashion in virtual landscapes treats clothing not as separate objects but as integral parts of the world itself. Drawing from fashion media's attention to materiality, styling, and the body, Costas builds environments that feel tactile and intimate despite their digital nature. Garments become part of the space's mood, shaping how movement feels and how bodies appear or disappear. Through game engines, fashion transcends physical limitations, creating silhouettes that breathe with landscapes and textures that blur the boundary between clothing and environment, presence and dissolution.
	</p>
</div>

